<h3>When DIY Makes Sense</h3>
<p>DIY works if you have the time to learn and execute. Use our <a href="/best/free-seo-tools/">free SEO tools</a> and follow a <a href="/blog/seo-new-website/">step-by-step SEO guide</a> to get started. The tradeoff is speed. A business owner spending 5 hours per week on SEO will produce 2 to 4 articles per month. A done for you service produces 30.</p>
<h3>When In-House Makes Sense</h3>
<p>Hiring a full-time SEO manager makes sense once your marketing budget exceeds $15,000 per month and you need dedicated, daily attention. Below that threshold, an in-house hire is the most expensive option per article produced.</p>
