<h2>How AI Changed Done for You SEO in 2026</h2>
<p>The done for you SEO market is worth <a href="https://www.mordorintelligence.com/industry-reports/seo-market">$83.98 billion in 2026</a> and growing at 12% per year. The biggest shift driving that growth is AI.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Done for you SEO ROI statistics" src="/images/blog/done-for-you-seo-roi-stats.webp" /></p>
<h3>What Changed</h3>
<p>Traditional done for you SEO meant hiring a team of writers, editors, and strategists. That model produced 4 to 8 articles per month at $1,500 to $5,000 per month. The cost per article ranged from $200 to $600.</p>
<p>AI-assisted done for you SEO changed the math. The same quality of optimized, research-backed content now costs $3 to $15 per article when produced at scale. That is what makes $99 per month for 30 articles possible.</p>
<h3>What Did Not Change</h3>
<p>Google's <a href="https://developers.google.com/search/docs/fundamentals/creating-helpful-content">official stance</a> is clear: content quality matters, not how it was produced. AI-generated content ranks the same as human-written content when it is helpful, accurate, and well-optimized.</p>
<p>What did not change is the need for strategy. AI generates content faster. It does not generate strategy. A done for you provider still needs keyword research, competitive analysis, <a href="/blog/build-topical-authority/">topical mapping</a>, and editorial oversight. The providers that skip strategy and publish raw AI output produce exactly the kind of content that <a href="https://ahrefs.com/blog/search-traffic-study/">96.55% of all pages</a> produce: content that gets zero traffic.</p>
