<h2>FAQ</h2>
<p><strong>What is done for you SEO?</strong></p>
<p>Done for you SEO is any arrangement where an external provider handles your search engine optimization. The provider manages keyword research, content creation, on-page optimization, technical SEO, and reporting. You review results and approve strategy. The provider does the work.</p>
<p><strong>How much does done for you SEO cost?</strong></p>
<p>Pricing ranges from $99 per month for automated content services to $10,000+ per month for enterprise agency retainers. The <a href="https://backlinko.com/seo-pricing">industry average</a> falls between $1,000 and $2,500 per month. Budget providers deliver content only. Premium providers deliver content plus technical SEO, link building, and dedicated account management.</p>
<p><strong>Is done for you SEO worth it for small businesses?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, for most small businesses. <a href="https://www.hirewithnear.com/blog/seo-outsourcing-statistics">74% of SMEs invest in SEO</a>, and the median ROI is 748%. The key is choosing a provider that delivers measurable results, not just activity reports. Organic search generates leads at roughly $31 each compared to $181 for paid ads.</p>
<p><strong>How long does done for you SEO take to work?</strong></p>
<p>Expect 3 to 6 months for early traction on long-tail keywords. Meaningful traffic and lead generation typically start between months 6 and 12. The SEO break-even period averages 6 to 12 months, but the compounding returns after that period make it one of the highest-ROI marketing channels available.</p>
<p><strong>What is the difference between done for you SEO and an SEO agency?</strong></p>
<p>An SEO agency is one type of done for you provider. But "done for you SEO" also includes automated platforms, freelancers, and hybrid models. The distinction is in execution. Agencies assign human teams to your account. Automated platforms use AI with human oversight to deliver at higher volume and lower cost. Both qualify as "done for you" if you are not doing the work yourself.</p>
<p><strong>How do I know if my SEO provider is doing a good job?</strong></p>
<p>Track 3 metrics in Google Search Console: organic impressions, average position, and click-through rate. All three should trend upward over a 90-day window. If your provider cannot show you these numbers monthly, they are hiding something. Use our free <a href="/tools/website-seo-score/">website SEO score</a> tool to check your current performance.</p>
<p>Done for you SEO is the fastest way for small and mid-size businesses to build organic traffic without building a marketing team. The providers that combine strategy, quality content, and automated publishing deliver the best results at the lowest cost.</p>
